by Imperivm Terrae » Wed Apr 15, 2020 10:22 pm

They're an Islamic state slapped right into the middle of India. From what I can tell, they were essentially a Princely State of the British Raj from around the fall of the Mughals until 1948, when the Fascists took over a now independent India (though I don't know why Fascism is popular given WWII seems to have happened). Of course, the Deccani didn't like India too much, so in 2024 they told them to piss off. Their majority religion is Islam, which puzzles me given that Hinduism is the dominant religion in the subcontinent outside Bangladesh and Pakistan even before the partition, but I won't question its possibility. Their Sultan is 19 at this point in real life, but their canon seems to be happening in 2056; then again, he began his reign at a pretty young (but not uncommon) age as a revolutionary leader.
